-- Egypt Secures 300 Million Riyals From Saudi Fund, MENA Reports
-- B y   S a l m a   E l   W a r d a n y
-- 2012-07-17T14:17:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/egypt-secures-300-million-riyals-from-saudi-fund-mena-reports.html
Egypt secured a 300 million riyal
($80 million) loan from the Saudi Fund for Development to
refurbish and replace irrigation pumps, the state-run Middle
East  News Agency  reported, citing Irrigation Minister Hisham
Kandil.  The project aims to improve irrigation for more than
200,000 feddans (208,000 acres) across the country, the Cairo-
based agency said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Salma El Wardany in Cairo at 
 selwardany@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  